          "tz": -360
        },
        "subject": "LU-13035 lnet: Use send_data fields to record next-hop",
        "message": "LU-13035 lnet: Use send_data fields to record next-hop\n\nUtilize the existing fields in the send_data struct to record the\nlnet_peer_ni and lnet_peer objects for the next-hop. That way we\ndon't need to pass pointers to lnet_handle_find_routed_path to\nrecord this information.\n\nSince we're already passing the entire send_data object, we can\nalso get rid of the dst_nid argument to lnet_handle_find_routed\npath, since this is already recorded in the send_data object.\n\nTest-Parameters: trivial\nSigned-off-by: Chris Horn <hornc@cray.com>\nChange-Id: I33e4862394879fea5ff38ffce0466b634d374027\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
